	h4.cd The Experience
	p.cd Since no magnetic materials can enter the MRI room, we designed a three step approach. The first is an iPod touch that establishes the story and allows for the child to make selections for the rest of their experience. Once ready to enter the MRI room, the iPod is removed and replaced with a the static transparency is visible. Without the iPod, the child can be moved to the MRI bed, but will still be entertained. Our static transparency is similar to the View-Master experience and could include a Where's Waldo game or a calming ocean scene to extend the story established by the iPod experience. THe third step is a projector system. Many MRI's have a long throw projector that is just outside the room and projects through a hole in the wall to a screen behind the MRI. By removing the screen, the projector can be extended directly onto a special projector screen on the goggles. Once finished, the process can be reversed as the child is brought back out to the hallway.

