	//- h4.cd Engineering Constraints
	//- p.cd There were many constraints in this design, such as designing a functional system without any electronic components, the tight space inside the MRI head coil, and patient comfort. Below are a few design highlights:

	h5.cd Transition-Friendly Design
	p.cd To allow a the technician to swap between the three modes seamlessly, we designed a paddle system that could allow quick modifications, but would still secure each successive item. First, the goggles were assembled with the phone slid in place and the static transparency snapped onto the front of the goggles. Once on the child's face, the phone could be slid out and the static image would be visible. Once on the MRI bed, the projector screens could be slid in, then the transparency slid off minimizing the down time in between transitions.

